{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011E4reAGhDc8VcqupSkmUdz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Findings: MockWalletProvider Connected/Disconnected State Management\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the codebase and found exactly how the MockWalletProvider determines connected vs disconnected wallet state. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### Key Files Located\n1. **MockWalletProvider.tsx** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx`\n2. **MockWalletState.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts`\n3. **WalletContext.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/context.ts`\n4. **types.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/types.ts`\n\n### localStorage Key\n**`\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\"`** (defined at line 17 of MockWalletState.ts)\n\n### localStorage Value Format\n```json\n{\n  \"address\": \"string (base58 encoded Solana public key)\",\n  \"balance\": \"number (in lamports)\"\n}\n```\n\nExample:\n```json\n{\n  \"address\": \"8PVb7MBvYSMfCq8d7nwPq4xvqV7x5gYqQKs6L9pRzJ2M\",\n  \"balance\": 1000000000\n}\n```\n\n### Connected vs Disconnected State\n\n**For Playwright tests to set connected state:**\n```javascript\n// To connect wallet\nlocalStorage.setItem('rng-utopia-mock-wallet', JSON.stringify({\n  address: \"8PVb7MBvYSMfCq8d7nwPq4xvqV7x5gYqQKs6L9pRzJ2M\",\n  balance: 1000000000  // 1 SOL in lamports\n}));\n```\n\n**To disconnect wallet:**\n```javascript\n// To disconnect wallet\nlocalStorage.removeItem('rng-utopia-mock-wallet');\n```\n\n### How It Works (Architecture)\n\n1. **Initial State** (line 24-29 of MockWalletProvider.tsx):\n   - `connected: false`\n   - `address: null`\n   - `publicKey: null`\n\n2. **On Mount** (lines 43-59):\n   - If `persistState: true` (default, see line 14 of MockWalletState.ts):\n     - Loads `localStorage.getItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\")`\n     - If found AND `autoConnect: true`, sets `connected: true`\n     - Otherwise stays `connected: false`\n\n3. **Connect Flow** (lines 71-105):\n   - First checks `loadPersistedState()` from localStorage\n   - If persisted state exists, reuses that address\n   - If not, generates new mock keypair\n   - Sets `connected: true`, `address: <publicKey>`, `publicKey: PublicKey`\n\n4. **Disconnect Flow** (lines 107-115):\n   - Clears localStorage (calls `clearPersistedState()`)\n   - Sets state back to `initialState` with `connected: false`\n\n### WalletState Interface\n```typescript\ninterface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n```\n\n### Default Configuration\nFrom `DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG` (line 10-15 of MockWalletState.ts):\n- `initialBalance: 1000` (SOL)\n- `autoConnect: false` (won't auto-connect even if localStorage has state)\n- `simulatedLatency: 500` (ms)\n- `persistState: true` (uses localStorage)\n\n### For Playwright Test Automation\n\n**To toggle connected state:**\n\n1. **Set to Connected:**\n   ```javascript\n   await page.evaluate(() => {\n     localStorage.setItem('rng-utopia-mock-wallet', JSON.stringify({\n       address: \"8PVb7MBvYSMfCq8d7nwPq4xvqV7x5gYqQKs6L9pRzJ2M\",\n       balance: 1000000000\n     }));\n   });\n   // Then reload page or trigger wallet connect flow\n   ```\n\n2. **Set to Disconnected:**\n   ```javascript\n   await page.evaluate(() => {\n     localStorage.removeItem('rng-utopia-mock-wallet');\n   });\n   ```\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- The component reads localStorage on mount via `loadPersistedState()` hook (lines 43-59)\n- Just setting localStorage is not enough - you may need to reload the page or call the `connect()` method\n- If `autoConnect: true` was configured on MockWalletProvider, it would auto-connect on mount\n- The `connecting` flag transitions to `true` during connection and `false` when complete (line 72, 96)\n- Balance persists in localStorage but is independent of connection state"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a91fcac (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34062\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 35185</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abe33f0b-f1dd-4b96-a953-f5438b0c7570","uuid":"889a6d91-ac5c-43b3-8abb-a744dabec96e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In the codebase at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/, find how the MockWalletProvider determines connected vs disconnected wallet state. Specifically:\n1. Search for `rng-utopia-mock-wallet` in the codebase\n2. Search for `MockWalletProvider` to understand how it works\n3. Search for any localStorage usage related to wallet state\n4. Look at how the wallet adapter context provides connected/disconnected state\n\nI need to know the exact localStorage key and values to set to toggle between connected and disconnected wallet states for Playwright tests.\n\nBe thorough - check all files in apps/platform/src/ related to wallet, mock, provider.","agentId":"a91fcac","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Findings: MockWalletProvider Connected/Disconnected State Management\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the codebase and found exactly how the MockWalletProvider determines connected vs disconnected wallet state. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### Key Files Located\n1. **MockWalletProvider.tsx** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx`\n2. **MockWalletState.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts`\n3. **WalletContext.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/context.ts`\n4. **types.ts** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/